(42, 19, 17, 66, 2, 26, 29, 'authority over ten cities', 'Authority and Faithfulness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the reward of authority given to those who are faithful in their responsibilities. In Luke, the faithful servant is granted authority over cities, while in Revelation, the overcomer is promised power over nations.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 17, 9, 2, 30, 30, 'thou good servant', 'Faithfulness and Divine Reward', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of reward for faithfulness. In Luke, the good servant is rewarded with authority for his faithfulness, while in 1 Samuel, God honors those who honor Him, suggesting a similar principle of divine recognition for loyalty.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 17, 60, 1, 7, 7, 'faithful in a very little', 'Faithfulness and Reward', 'This connection highlights the theme of faithfulness leading to greater rewards. In Luke, the faithful servant is given authority over cities, while in 1 Peter, the trial of faith is shown to yield praise and honor at Christ''s appearing.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 17, 1, 39, 4, 4, 'thou good servant', 'Faithfulness and Authority', 'This connection highlights the theme of faithfulness leading to increased authority. In both passages, a servant''s faithfulness results in being entrusted with greater responsibilities.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 17, 46, 4, 5, 5, 'faithful in a very little', 'Faithfulness and Divine Reward', 'This connection highlights the theme of faithfulness leading to greater responsibility and reward. Both passages emphasize that those who are faithful in small matters will be recognized and praised by God at the appropriate time.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 18, 40, 13, 23, 23, 'thy pound hath gained five pounds', 'Fruitfulness and Growth', 'This connection highlights the theme of productivity in both passages. In Luke, the servant''s pound gaining five pounds reflects the idea of fruitful investment, while in Matthew, the seed on good ground bears fruit in varying amounts, emphasizing growth and return.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 18, 41, 4, 20, 20, NULL, 'Fruitfulness and Growth', 'This connection highlights the theme of productivity and growth in both passages. In Luke, the servant''s pound gains five pounds, while in Mark, the good ground yields fruit in varying amounts, emphasizing the importance of fruitful outcomes.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 18, 47, 8, 12, 12, NULL, 'Willingness and Results in Service', 'This connection highlights the theme of productivity in service. Both passages emphasize the importance of what one has gained or is willing to give, reflecting a principle of stewardship and accountability.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 19, 46, 15, 58, 58, 'Be thou also over five cities', 'Stewardship and Labor in the Lord', 'This connection highlights the theme of faithful stewardship in both passages. Luke 19:19 speaks of being over five cities, while 1 Corinthians 15:58 encourages abounding in the work of the Lord, emphasizing that labor is not in vain.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 19, 23, 3, 10, 10, NULL, 'Righteousness and Reward', 'Both passages emphasize the idea of reward for faithful actions. In Luke, being ''over five cities'' suggests a reward for service, while Isaiah assures that the righteous will ''eat the fruit of their doings,'' indicating a positive outcome for their actions.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 19, 46, 3, 8, 8, NULL, 'Reward for Faithful Service', 'This connection highlights the theme of reward based on one''s labor. Both passages emphasize the idea that individuals will receive rewards according to their efforts and faithfulness in service.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 19, 47, 9, 6, 6, NULL, 'Connection of Stewardship and Reward', 'This connection highlights the principle of reward based on one''s actions. Both passages emphasize that the measure of one''s efforts, whether in stewardship or sowing, directly influences the outcome received.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 19, 63, 1, 8, 8, NULL, 'Faithfulness and Reward', 'This connection highlights the theme of stewardship and reward. In Luke 19:19, being ''over five cities'' suggests a reward for faithfulness, while 2 John 1:8 emphasizes the importance of maintaining one''s efforts to receive a ''full reward.''', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 20, 20, 26, 13, 16, 'here is thy pound, which I have kept', 'Connection of Slothfulness and Accountability', 'This connection highlights the theme of slothfulness in both passages. The servant in Luke 19:20 kept his pound laid up, similar to the slothful man in Proverbs who avoids action and responsibility.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 20, 40, 25, 24, 24, NULL, 'Parable of the Talents Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of stewardship and accountability in both passages. Each servant presents what they have kept, reflecting their understanding of their master''s expectations.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 20, 42, 3, 9, 9, NULL, 'Fruitfulness and Accountability', 'This connection highlights the theme of accountability for one''s actions. In both passages, there is an emphasis on the consequences of not producing good results, whether it be keeping a pound laid up or failing to bear good fruit.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 20, 42, 6, 46, 46, 'Lord', 'Responsibility and Obedience', 'This connection highlights the theme of accountability in both passages. The servant in Luke 19:20 presents his pound, indicating a failure to act, while Luke 6:46 questions the sincerity of calling Jesus ''Lord'' without obedience to His commands.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 20, 59, 4, 17, 17, NULL, 'Responsibility in Faithfulness', 'This connection highlights the theme of accountability in both passages. In Luke, the servant''s failure to invest the pound reflects neglect of responsibility, while James emphasizes that knowing to do good without action is sin.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 21, 40, 25, 24, 25, 'I feared thee, because thou art an austere man', 'Connection of Fear and Judgment', 'Both passages emphasize the fear of the master due to his perceived harshness. The phrases ''austere man'' and ''hard man'' reflect similar characterizations of the master, leading to the servants'' actions of hiding their talents.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 21, 2, 20, 19, 20, NULL, 'Fear of God and Accountability', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of fear in relation to authority. In Luke, the servant''s fear of the master reflects a similar fear of God expressed in Exodus, where the people fear direct communication with God.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 21, 9, 6, 19, 21, 'I feared thee', 'Fear of God''s Judgment', 'This connection highlights the theme of fear in the presence of God''s authority. In both passages, there is a recognition of the seriousness of God''s actions and the consequences of disobedience, leading to lamentation and a sense of unworthiness.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 21, 9, 12, 20, 20, NULL, 'Fear and Service to God', 'This connection highlights the theme of fear in relation to serving God. In Luke, fear of an austere man leads to inaction, while in 1 Samuel, the call is to serve the Lord wholeheartedly despite past wickedness.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 21, 10, 6, 9, 11, 'I feared thee', 'Fear of the Lord', 'This connection highlights the theme of fear in both passages. In Luke, the servant expresses fear of an austere master, while David''s fear of the Lord leads him to reconsider the presence of the ark.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 21, 18, 21, 14, 15, 'I feared thee, because thou art an austere man', 'Fear of God''s Authority', 'This connection highlights the fear and rejection of God''s authority present in both passages. In Luke, the servant''s fear of the master reflects a misunderstanding of God''s nature, while in Job, the desire to distance from God indicates a similar rejection of His ways.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 21, 26, 18, 25, 29, NULL, 'Justice and Accountability in God', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of accountability for one''s actions. In Luke, the servant fears the master for his strictness, while Ezekiel addresses the perceived inequality of God''s justice, affirming that individuals are responsible for their choices.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 22, 10, 1, 16, 16, NULL, 'Judgment Based on Testimony', 'This connection highlights the theme of judgment based on one''s own words. Both passages emphasize how the speaker''s own mouth serves as evidence against them, leading to their condemnation.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 22, 18, 15, 5, 6, NULL, 'Condemnation by One''s Own Words', 'This connection highlights how both passages emphasize self-condemnation through one''s own speech. In Luke, the servant''s own words are used against him, paralleling Job''s assertion that one''s mouth testifies against them.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 22, 40, 12, 37, 37, 'Out of thine own mouth will I judge thee', 'Judgment Based on Words', 'This connection highlights the theme of judgment based on one''s own words. Both passages emphasize that individuals will be judged according to what they have said or acknowledged.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
